---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <article class="cv-content">
    <!-- Summary -->
    <section id="summary" class="cv-section">
      <h2>Summary</h2>

      <p class="cv-location">Saint Petersburg, remote or hybrid</p>
      <p class="cv-summary">
        Engineering Manager / Acting CTO. 10+ years of management (4 teams, up
        to 22 engineers), 17+ years in web development. Building teams and
        processes, scaling platforms, connecting business and technology.
      </p>

      <h3 class="cv-subsection-title">Selected impact:</h3>
      <ul class="cv-impact-list">
        <li>
          Built team and product requirements from scratch → MVP in production
          in 9 months.
        </li>
        <li>Unit migration to AWS without OPEX increase → SLA 99.97%</li>
        <li>
          Implemented shared observability framework and centralized traffic
          routing, MTTR −20%
        </li>
        <li>
          Decommissioned legacy systems and migrated users → ~−1% of revenue
          costs for support.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built management vertical: established team leads in 4 teams,
          implemented on-call/regulations; conducted 2 security audits without
          critical findings
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="cv-summary">
        Ready to take on technical leadership of a unit up to 50 engineers: org
        design, people management, delivery, reliability. Format: Remote/Hybrid,
        SPb; full-time or fractional.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Competencies -->
    <section id="competencies" class="cv-section">
      <h2>Key Competencies</h2>

      <div class="cv-competency">
        <h3>Leadership Skills and People Management</h3>
        <p>
          I adapt my management style to the team's maturity and context,
          striving for Servant Leadership while maintaining flexibility. Tools
          I've used: regular 1-1s, performance reviews, 360 feedback, skip-level
          meetings, individual development plans, competency matrices.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-competency">
        <h3>Communication and Influence</h3>
        <p>
          I advocate for asynchronous communication and documentation,
          understanding that sometimes meetings are necessary, in which case
          they should have a clear agenda. I believe in "quiet influence." I
          have experience in conflict resolution, translating between business
          and technical language, facilitation, and mediation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-competency">
        <h3>Architecture and Infrastructure</h3>
        <p>
          Microservices architecture, Event-driven architecture, API Design
          (REST, GraphQL), DevOps practices (CI/CD, observability).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-competency">
        <h3>Technical Stack</h3>
        <p>
          Python, Ruby, Go, Typescript, Postgres, Docker, Kafka, worked with a
          large number of technologies and tools within web development.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-competency">
        <h3>Management Framework</h3>
        <p>
          Agile (Scrum, Kanban) methodologies and the theory of constraints are
          closest to me. Main tool experience — Atlassian ecosystem (JIRA,
          Confluence, etc.) combined with Slack.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Experience -->
    <section id="experience" class="cv-section">
      <h2>Work Experience</h2>

      <div class="cv-job">
        <h3>Aviasales / Travelpayouts</h3>
        <p class="cv-job-period">Dec 2009 - Aug 2025 (15y 8m)</p>
        <p class="cv-job-growth">
          Growth: Junior → Middle → Senior → Tech/Frontend TL → Product Manager
          → Engineering Manager → Head of Technology.
        </p>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Head of Technology</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">Jan 2023 - Aug 2025 (2y 7m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              4 teams, up to 22 engineers, over 5 major projects, over 30
              microservices and microfrontends
            </li>
            <li>
              Formed an engineering team for a new flagship AI tools product.
            </li>
            <li>
              Restructured engineering teams within product teams: introduced
              team leads in all teams, balanced team workload across projects,
              and optimized team composition for business requirements. This
              reduced idle time and increased development throughput.
            </li>
            <li>
              Formed and launched an integrations team (technical accounting).
            </li>
            <li>Responsible for unit infrastructure budgeting.</li>
            <li>
              Led technical integration of enterprise partners with Aviasales.
            </li>
            <li>
              Led the unit's migration to AWS cloud infrastructure, migrated
              without increasing infrastructure costs, achieving ~20%
              improvement in static content delivery speed and availability
              increase to 99.97%.
            </li>
            <li>
              Initiated implementation and deployment of common approaches to
              observability and traffic routing. This reduced average incident
              resolution time by 20%.
            </li>
            <li>Implemented on-call duties and created duty regulations.</li>
            <li>
              Together with security engineers and external contractors,
              conducted two security audits that found no critical
              vulnerabilities.
            </li>
            <li>
              Developed an action plan and preparatory measures for crisis
              situations such as RKN blockings or the need for unit isolation.
            </li>
            <li>
              Prepared and implemented partner network integration with the
              "advertising law" in accordance with business and legal department
              requirements.
            </li>
            <li>
              Led development and brought to production several major projects:
              "advertising law," new Whitelabel (outsourced), MVP sales boost
              tool (5% revenue growth in first quarter), new tool delivery
              system (+20% installation conversion).
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Engineering Manager</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">Mar 2022 - Jan 2023 (10m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Led implementation of custom partner program for Aviasales' new
              brand in the US market, launched under tight deadlines. Delivered
              everything on time and in full scope.
            </li>
            <li>
              Technical debt quarter: 10+ engineers under direct management,
              gathered context, broke down into initiatives, organized working
              groups. As a result, several projects significantly reduced
              maintenance costs, several projects were deprecated, saving ~1%
              Revenue.
            </li>
            <li>
              Coordinated cross-team interactions, was responsible for
              cross-team initiative architecture and conflict resolution.
            </li>
            <li>
              Together with HR, implemented a competency matrix for engineers.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Product manager</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">Nov 2020 - Mar 2022 (1y 4m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Planned MVP functionality and basic architecture of a new product
              from scratch. Aligned the plan with stakeholders.
            </li>
            <li>Assembled a team: 3 frontend engineers and 2 backend.</li>
            <li>
              In 9 months, the team implemented MVP and launched it to
              production for beta testing.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Tech lead / Frontend Team lead</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">Mar 2016 - Nov 2020 (4y 7m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Managed 5–7 frontend engineers, first within one team, then after
              dividing into directions, across multiple teams.
            </li>
            <li>
              Developed many embeddable widgets, then actively promoted
              development of a universal SDK and implemented its core. As a
              result, new widgets were created with minimal development
              involvement.
            </li>
            <li>
              Adapted the core of Aviasales search engine for Whitelabel
              solution.
            </li>
            <li>
              Coordinated technical integrations with enterprise partners such
              as MegaFon, Tema.ru, Sheremetyevo, Pulkovo, Tinkoff, etc.
            </li>
            <li>
              Played a key role in splitting the unit monolith into
              microservices.
            </li>
            <li>
              Actively participated in implementing DevOps practices in the
              company, particularly introduced CI/CD pipeline and
              containerization of frontend projects within the unit.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Senior Software Engineer</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">May 2013 - Mar 2016 (2y 10m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Separation of Travelpayouts unit from Aviasales, lead role.</li>
            <li>
              Implemented many widgets and the first Aviasales Whitelabel.
            </li>
            <li>
              Played a key role in implementing metrics and A/B mechanism.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-position">
          <h4>Junior/Middle Software Engineer</h4>
          <p class="cv-position-period">Dec 2009 - May 2013 (3y 5m)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Responsible for Aviasales content engine (over 100,000 pages),
              implemented caching, speeding up content loading/generation 3x.
              Automated position analysis and content adjustment, achieved top
              positions in search engines with 80% of service traffic being
              organic.
            </li>
            <li>Worked on migrating the search engine from PHP to Ruby.</li>
            <li>
              Played a key role in planning and implementing high-performance
              in-memory price cache and wrote UI for it.
            </li>
            <li>
              Created the first embeddable Aviasales search widgets and the
              first version of back-office for partners.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Education and Certifications -->
    <section id="education" class="cv-section">
      <h2>Education and Certifications</h2>
      <ul class="cv-education-list">
        <li>
          <strong>2005 - 2010</strong> BSTU "Voenmekh", master's degree in Information
          Systems and Technologies
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2017</strong> MIPT & Yandex: "Mathematics and Python for Data Analysis",
          "Supervised Learning", "Finding Structure in Data"
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2018</strong> Product Heroes Course (Ilya Krasinsky's course):
          product management and unit economics
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2019</strong> GoPractice: Data-driven product management
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2023</strong> "Public Speaking" course by Victoria Bychkova
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2025</strong> Maxim Spiridonov's Workshop "Looking to the Future:
          Trends That Will Change the Future"
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

